    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The <ref refid="classDali_1_1WindowData" kindref="compound">WindowData</ref> class is used as a parameter for the constructors of the <ref refid="classDali_1_1Application" kindref="compound">Application</ref> class. The data from the <ref refid="classDali_1_1WindowData" kindref="compound">WindowData</ref> object is used to customize the default window created by the <ref refid="classDali_1_1Application" kindref="compound">Application</ref> class.</para>
<para>The default values are below: PositionSize : x:0, y:0, w:0, h:0 (full-screen window) Transparency : true (<ref refid="classDali_1_1Window" kindref="compound">Window</ref> is created with 32-bit color depth) WindowType : NORMAL mIsFrontBufferRendering : false</para>
<para>If you want to customize the window, you can modify the values of the <ref refid="classDali_1_1WindowData" kindref="compound">WindowData</ref> object as needed. @SINCE_2_2.23 </para>
    </detaileddescription>
